title: Persuasive or Deceptive Visualization?
description: Throughout this project, I used visualizations to explore the idea of persuasive and deceptive visualizations. The proposition I argued for and against was "Favoring increasing renewable energy production over nonrenewable energy production is more beneficial for strengthening the GDP of the United States."

title: Visualization Design
description: In this project, I used various sketches to guide the visualization design process, and then based on those sketches, found the best features and implemented them into a main visualization.

title: Exploratory Visual Analysis
description: Based on the theme "Housing for the Rich" for the Boston metropolitan area, I performed exploratory visual analysis of the data and then explored three different overall analysis questions through visualizations.
